tldr: The user requested a review of the sleep questionnaire application against
  its acceptance criteria and the implementation of missing features. The agent
  successfully implemented a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection,
  insufficient sleep syndrome detection, outbound links, weighted EDS scoring,
  and expanded CSV export. It also began implementing pain and chronic fatigue
  screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, requesting that any identified missing features be implemented.
  The agent systematically addressed several key areas. It introduced a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical safety warnings for high
  scores. Detection and tailored recommendations for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia
  and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome were integrated into the
  report generation. The agent also added a dedicated section for outbound links
  to various sleep and mental health resources. To enhance diagnostic accuracy,
  a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) was
  implemented. Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was significantly
  expanded to include all flattened questionnaire responses, providing more
  comprehensive data access. The agent also began the process of adding pain
  severity questions and chronic fatigue screening, demonstrating a thorough
  approach to meeting the specified acceptance criteria.
